cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY 

This paper involves learning physical dynamics from visual input, which suggests it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a model for learning in a counterfactual setting, which involves reasoning and decision-making, indicating it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of deep learning models and end-to-end learning suggests it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The synthetic 3D environment and the focus on physical systems suggest it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) or systems and control (cs.SY) categories.
